Getting Information about Pascal:
     To do this, press SHIFT-divide (hold down the SHIFT key and press the
key with the divide symbol, on the keypad at the right of the ICON
keyboard).  ALICE will list a menu of topics upon which it can offer help.
There will be a selection for whatever Pascal construct the cursor
currently rests on, whatever contains that construct, the container of the
container, and so on.  If you choose any of these topics, you will get a
description of that part of the Pascal language.
|mFor more, choose
|iDo nothing,nop
|iPascal programs,Hpnode/pascal_progr
|iThe PHELP command,Hcommand/phelp
|p
